  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Almond Gelatin Squares in Fruit</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Breakfast</cat>
        <cat>Fruits</cat>
        <cat>Low fat</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Unflavored Gelatin</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Cold Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Boiling Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Nonfat Dry Milk</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Almond Extract</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Ground Cinnamon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Pear; peeled,cored,cubed</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Seedless Red Grapes</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Kiwi Fruit; peeled and sliced</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Orange; peeled,sectioned</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Pineapple Chunks</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Orange Juice</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  In a small saucepan, combine the gelatin and cold water. Add the boiling
  water and stir until the gelatin is completely dissolved. Place over medium
  heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Gradually whisk in the dry
  milk and sugar and return to a boil. Stir in the almond extract and
  cinnamon. When the cinnamon is dissolved, pour the mixture into an 8 inch
  square pan. Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
  
  In a large bowl, combine the pear, grapes, kiwifruits, orange, pineapple
  and orange juice. Gently toss to mix well.
  
  To serve, cut the gelatin into 1 inch squares, add to the fruit and toss
  gently. Divide among 4 individual bowls.
  
  NOTES : Kiwifruits, oranges and pineapples are all excellent sources of
  vitamin C.
  Recipe by: Jane Fonda Cooking For Healthy Living
  
